OL,6,FIn a trial of the facts, the
OL,7,Fprosecution sets our the case to the
OL,8,Fjury who decide if the defendant
OL,9,Fcommitted the offences - but the
OL,10,Fdefendant is not part of the
OL,11,Fproceedings and verdicts cannot result
OL,12,Fin criminal convictions.
OL,14,FAfter hearing the evidence over five
OL,15,Fdays, the jurors deliberated for
OL,16,Faround 40 minutes before unanimously
OL,17,Fruling that John unlawfully inflicted
OL,18,Ffatal neck and head injuries on her
OL,19,Fchildren and stabbed her husband in
OL,20,Fthe stomach.
